      "writtenOn": "2019-04-10T18:19:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, we could have implemented this in Skottie, and expose a more general sksg::TableColorFilter at this level.\n\nThere\u0027s an efficiency downside to that: under the current Skottie architecture, each animated property is being pushed to SG independently - so if e.g. two levels-related properties are being animated, we may end up re-computing and pushing the table twice per tick.  To fix we\u0027d need two separate update-props/sync-to-SG passes - which is doable but I\u0027ve been kicking that refactor down the road so far.\n\nI don\u0027t have a strong opinion about native Skia, but since it devolves to a table CF and I don\u0027t trust the semantics to be stabilized yet I\u0027m leaning on the non-native side.",
      "parentUuid": "f9997378_670cbe0c",
